      "content": "Even a single dose of ibuprofen can be problematic for people with chronic kidney disease. The kidneys don't have a lot of filtering capacity, so even small amounts of ibuprofen can cause damage. It's not about the risk of messing things up more, it's about the potential to trigger a kidney crisis. A single headache pill could lead to a temporary but potentially serious kidney issue.",
